// Per-index failure policies on chained multi-dimensional indexing — each `[i]` carries its OWN
// policy, which the former comma form `a[i, j]` could not express (a single bracket, one policy).
// Here the ROW index 99 is `!clamp`ed to the last valid row (no abort), then the column index 0 reads
// it. M's last row is {4,5,6}, so `M[99] !clamp [0]` == 4. (The row index is now bounds-checked at
// all — it formerly read out of bounds unchecked.)
// RUN: %arche build -o %t %s && %t | grep -x "4"
#import { fmt }
M :: { { 1, 2, 3 }, { 4, 5, 6 } }
;
main :: proc() {
  fmt.printf("%d\n", M[99] !clamp[0]);
}
